bib_record.title: Inelastic scattering of protons from B-10 between 5 and 16.5 MeV.

0.free_text: the average of the measured yields between 85.                                     and  90. degr.

free_txt: Six cooled solid-state detectors mounted in the
18-in. scattering chamber were used.
The error in the absolute normalization
The absolute cross-sections were obtained by
normalizing these data to the cross section measured at
10 MeV. It was required that the sum of total cross
sections for the 1.74-, 2.15-, and 3.59-MeV states
be the same for both sets of data.
The absolute normalization was also checked by
assuming that at extreme forward angles (< 10.degr.)
at bombarding energies between 4 and 5 MeV, the
elastic cross section is totally due to
Rutherford scattering.
Self-supporting 10B targets (95% enrichment), 100-300
mu-g/cm**2 thick.
